Clothing Appl. U. S. Merchandise Mart\nB. F Goodrich tltb and t St. it Kemps TV \u00bble\u00bb\u00ab\"delo 3tt# Wltaan Blvd drllaftaa\nmis Rhndc i.i.nd Aw n z Teochum\u2019s TV t;pn M.vlbarn Pik.. ratal Hill. Dominion TV Vienna TV\nHersowA Auto Radio Kdnt TV si\" T.V vSLwST'IIS\nnth BBid o Rtk N H ItnH.AgfN UNiffr M \u00ab\u00bbiii Villi\u00abt P?,,!!\u201e;!* T\u00bb\n\u25a0a- IfhOl Indian HpbU Id HI. EulPfPfr. U. Atrrllnff. VP.\nHe^ x Jew\u00ablcr\u00bb Watts-Berry Lonsburghs Department Stora Early Bird Buying Service Wonderly's TV\nMM.% M %t gn H St. ft.ft UntlFf A\u00ab|.Y miumbia Pik\u00ab trttPftPfi r\u00bbp9tt\u00bbF6\nJordon, Inc Willi* Wilson, Inc. Morlboro Electric Supply C*. Sol Feldman Firestone Stora Trennary Brolheia j\nAn.-n Ovarii, to. N PEA r at. N.W to par Uarlbarn M. u.lkaae 9ookar BUI W. *W\nbusiness cycles since the end\nof World War L\nDr Moore was quoted by the\nNew York Times as saying the\ncurrent recession, which started\nin July last year, now appears\nto rank as an \u201cintermediate or\nmoderate\u201d recession when com\npared with other \"mild\u201d recee\nj sions of recent times.\nCould Alter Picture\nHe noted that governmental\nmeasures to moderate the re\ncession could alter the picture\nforecast by statistics to date.\nThe studies involve two sets\nof indicators. One group shows\ndeclines in various sectors of\nthe economy since the start of\nthe current recession. The\nother group is considered an in\ndicator of future business ac\ntivity.\nIn the former group are stat\nistics measuring non-farm em\nployment. changes in the per\ncentage of the labor force un\nemployed, physical volume of\nindustrial production, bank\ndebits outside New York, per\nsonal Income and retail sales.\nThese Indicators show the\n1957-58 recession as slightly\nmilder during its first six\nmonths than those which\nstarted in 1953 and 1948.\nHowever, most of the second i\ngroup of Indicators forecasting:\nfuture activity show sharper\ndeclines in store than were suf\nfered in the 1953 and 1948 re\ncessions.\nDurable Goads Drop\nIncluded in this group are,\nthe average work week in man- 1\nufaeturing, new orders for dur-!\nable goods, residential con- 1\nstruetlon contracts, commercial\nand industrial construction\ncontracts, new incorporations,\nliabilities of business failures,\nbasic commodity prices and in\ndustrial stock prices.\nFor example. Dr. Moore's\ncharts show that from last July\nto last January new orders for\ndurable goods dropped 19.3 per\ncent.\nDuring the first six months\nof the J 953-54 recession the\ndrop was only 18.2 per cent.\nI DRAFTSMEN\u2019S I\np SUPPLIES\nMUTH\n1332 N.Y. Ave. N.W. ST. 34323\nand during the first six months\nof the 1948-49 recession. Orders\ndropped only 17.9 per cent.\nfar sin Adroedsf\nWELL-PAID\u2014\nHotel Position\nIn laar Spmrm Tlnm\nWo \u201ccertify\" you will \u201cmoko food\u201d\not we Ofsist in placing yeu in yeur\nchoice es Hotel, Motel. Club or\n,j| Institutional petition, through our\nj notion-wide Placement Bureau ot\njj ne extra cost.\nH Day b Evening Clotaat New\nForming or Study at Hama\nI Contoct ui Monday through Friday, j!\nB8:30 A.M. to 4:00 fM fvonings L\nand Saturday by of\u00dfpointmoot. Ap l{\nproved for Veterans Training, Visit, f'\nPhene er Write for PBCB book I Ask\nfor Mrs. Sinn. 0\nLIWIS\nhotel trainiHf school\ntins Sueceulul Yfr\nP 2301 Pa. Art. N.W.\nPI. 3-4692","height":"28676","width":"18414"}}
